This paper involves computer vision techniques for real-time stylization using neural networks, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as conditional instance normalization and learning embeddings, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the structure and organization of semantic information, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
